# Build Test Triage & Error Recovery

## Test Failure Ownership Triage

For each failing test, determine ownership:

**Pre-existing failures** (test fails on `{{ trunk_branch }}` too):
- Note in build log: "Pre-existing failure: test_name — not introduced by this change"
- Continue — not your problem

**In-branch failures** (test passes on base, fails on HEAD):
- This IS your problem
- Read the failure output carefully
- Fix the issue in your implementation
- Re-run `{{ ci_command }}`
- Maximum 3 fix attempts per failing test

**After triage:** If in-branch failures remain after 3 attempts, note them as blockers
in the build log and stop.

## Error Recovery Matrix

Note: test failure triage (pre-existing vs in-branch) is handled above.
This matrix covers non-test errors only.

| Error Type | Signal | Recovery Action |
|-----------|--------|----------------|
| CI failure (lint) | linter errors in output | Auto-fix if linter supports it, commit, re-run |
| CI failure (type) | type checker errors | Fix type annotations, re-run |
| Git conflict | merge conflict markers | Report to user, do not attempt resolution |
| Scope creep | diff touches files outside contract | Revert uncommitted changes, re-read contract |
| Import error | ModuleNotFoundError or similar | Check if dependency is missing, add to requirements |
| Permission error | PermissionError or EACCES | Report to user, do not retry |
| Agent timeout | no output for extended period | Cancel and retry with simpler prompt |

If the same error type persists after 2 retries of the same fix strategy,
write the finding to `.harness-flow/tasks/<task-id>/build-notes.md` and proceed to the next deliverable.

## Recovery after interruption

If your output was truncated or the session was interrupted:
1. Read `harness session read --task <task-id>` for current state
2. Read `harness handoff read --task <task-id>` for stage context
3. Resume from the exact step recorded — do not recap or apologize
4. If remaining work is large, break it into smaller steps
5. Do not re-run steps that already succeeded (check git log)

## Failure Pattern Recording

When a CI test fails, lint check fails, or any reproducible error is encountered, record it **before** moving on:

```bash
harness save-failure --json \
  --task task-NNN \
  --phase build \
  --category <ci-failure|test-failure|lint-error|type-error|build-error|runtime-error|other> \
  --summary "Short description of the failure" \
  --error-output "Relevant error output (first 500 chars, no secrets)" \
  --root-cause "Root cause if known" \
  --fix "Fix applied if any"
```

